# Project Name

Brief description of your project here.

## Prerequisites

Before you begin, ensure you have met the following requirements:
- Python 3.x installed
- Git (optional, if you plan to clone a Git repository)

## Setting Up Your Development Environment

This project uses a virtual environment to manage dependencies. Follow the steps below according to your operating system to set up your development environment.

### Windows (PowerShell)

1. Open PowerShell and navigate to your project directory:
    ```bash
    cd path\to\your\project
    ```

2. Create a virtual environment:
    ```bash
    python -m venv venv
    ```

3. Activate the virtual environment:
    ```bash
    .\venv\Scripts\Activate
    ```

### Windows (Git Bash)

1. Open Git Bash and navigate to your project directory:
    ```bash
    cd path/to/your/project
    ```

2. Create a virtual environment:
    ```bash
    python -m venv venv
    ```

3. Activate the virtual environment:
    ```bash
    source venv/Scripts/activate
    ```

### macOS (zsh)

1. Navigate to your project directory:
    
    cd path/to/your/project
   

2. Create a virtual environment:
    
    python3 -m venv venv
    

3. Activate the virtual environment:

    source venv/bin/activate

## Installing Dependencies

After setting up the virtual environment, install the project dependencies:

pip install -r requirements.txt
